<h3 id="star-trek-comparison">Star Trek Comparison</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Recall Lecture 16</li>
  <li>How to write the comparison essay on these:
    <ul>
      <li>One paragraph: Ultimate Computer (M5)</li>
      <li>Second Paragraph: Measure of a Man (Data)</li>
      <li>Similar texts will make this assignment harder</li>
      <li>NOTE: The transition between these two paragraphs should be the
  similarities</li>
      <li>Close analysis includes quotes and description of scenes</li>
      <li>Aim for 20-30 quotes</li>
      <li>Description of scenes are important too
        <ul>
          <li>What kind of spacing is there?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Think about the time period in which the texts were produced in</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Technology
    <ul>
      <li>Spock admires M5‚Äôs competence as a slave, but does not wish to serve under
  it.</li>
      <li>Next Generation:
        <ul>
          <li>What is the relationship between man and machine?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Both looking at the impact of a new technology
        <ul>
          <li>There are no other Data‚Äôs or M5‚Äôs</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Ethics
    <ul>
      <li>Ultimate Computer
        <ul>
          <li>‚ÄúI have no wish to serve under [computers], Captian‚Äù</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Measure of a Man
        <ul>
          <li>What are computers‚Äô rights?</li>
          <li>Are machines slaves? Should they be?</li>
          <li>What does society value?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Class
    <ul>
      <li>Ultimate Computer
        <ul>
          <li>How is the top of the social hierarchy effected by techonolgy?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Measure of a Man
        <ul>
          <li>How is the bottom of the social hierarchy effected by techonolgy?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Similarities
        <ul>
          <li>Computers are used so that humans don‚Äôt have to do dangerous work.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Conflict
    <ul>
      <li>Ultimate Computer
        <ul>
          <li>Man vs man</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Measure of a Man
        <ul>
          <li>Man vs self</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Gender
    <ul>
      <li>Ultimate Computer
        <ul>
          <li>1 female character
            <ul>
              <li>Capitan addresses her by rank</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>She interupts and corrects the captian which shows her authority</li>
          <li>‚Äúthere are some things men much do to remain men‚Äù</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Measure of a Man
        <ul>
          <li>Significantly more female characters with obvious status</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Race
    <ul>
      <li>Ultimate Computer
