<h2 id="breakout-rooms-answer-questions-on-chapter">Breakout Rooms: Answer Questions on Chapter</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Group 1
    <ul>
      <li>Peter Travers‚Äô Review on the Girl with The Dragon Tattoo</li>
      <li>How is their impression created?</li>
      <li>Notes how the editing and production was good</li>
      <li>More implicit on what he‚Äôs suggesting</li>
      <li>Anything that‚Äôs not negative is positive</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Group 2
    <ul>
      <li>What does Travers say that the film is missing?</li>
      <li>Didn‚Äôt think it was daring enough
        <ul>
          <li>Didn‚Äôt push social bounderies</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Wasn‚Äôt as good as other works by the director</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Group 3
    <ul>
      <li>Historical context for reviews (like we saw in the profile unit) is good
        <h1 id="lecture-22---introduction-to-review-drafts-11-18-20">Lecture 22 - Introduction to Review Drafts (11-18-20)</h1>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>2020-11-18</p>

<p>The Difference between Greta Van Fleet‚Äôs Review and Guy Fieri‚Äôs Restaurant
Review:</p>

<h2 id="guy-fieris-restaurant">Guy Fieri‚Äôs Restaurant</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Personal Experience with restaurant</li>
  <li>Explains why every aspect of the restaurant is bad</li>
  <li>Calling out Guy Fieri specifically</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="greta-van-fleet">Greta Van Fleet</h2>

<ul>
  <li>More historical context</li>
  <li>Going against popular opinion at the time</li>
  <li>The essence of the band is just going off of Led Zeppelin
    <ul>
      <li>Just going off of nostalgia</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 id="outline-for-review">Outline for Review</h2>

<ul>
  <li>People usually read reviews with an opinion already in mind
    <ul>
      <li>Can upset you because reviews often don‚Äôt give both sides</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>You can do whatever you want in your own review
    <ul>
      <li>As long as you have criteria</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Needs a dominate impression
    <ul>
      <li>And a call to action</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Because this is for the public‚Äôs view, if can be more informal.
    <ul>
      <li>Have creative liberty (can have sentence fragments, etc.)
        <ul>
          <li>Just avoid cliches</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Needs in Image at the beginning</li>
  <li>Where are you going to bring in your research?</li>
  <li>Justified text</li>
  <li>MadLib for what we‚Äôre doing</li>
</ul>

<p>Example:
I am going to write about Tim Minchin‚Äôs new album Apart Together. Apart Together
is an example of a singer songwriter album. Another example of a singer
songwriter and R&amp;B is Awaken, my Love by Childish Gambino (Donald Glover).</p>

